narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: This course covered expansive new grounds for me in terms of historical and thematic content. I do not think I have stepped away from any other course in my time here and felt so transformed, so matured by the work. In addition to historical material, Professor Allen also continued her commitments to making her students better readers, writers, and discussants, and for that I am also incredibly grateful.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, very much so. Although focused on postwar German history, the content of the course proves relevant across many time periods and disciplines. This era, particularly as framed and taught by Professor Allen, ought to be fascinating to many backgrounds.
